it has reached triple digits where i live and is too hot to take the kids outside my toddler is getting cranky from being stuck inside he has grown bored with indoor activities like finger painting coloring cartoons etc does anyone have any suggestions on indoor activites to keep him from getting bored and to help me keep my sanity if he is old enough to wrestle around with try that it will burn off all kinds of enegy he will be more satisfied when he drinks and eats too he will not be nearly as fussy don't tickle him wrestle him he will not know what to think at first but he will get into it let him clamor around on you as if he is winning then pin him keep goofing off with him and he will adore you let him win every once in a while he will be delighted he just pinned mom to the floor wow when he goes to sleep he will sleep like an angel when he wakes up he will not be as cranky either that and he knows that you will wrestle and tussle with him when he needs it when the sun goes down take him for a decent walk if you get tired while walking just remember he will be tired too let him take a coke with him do not make it a chore make it something that starts to close the day he will learn to expect it and will look forward to it kids are furnaces of energy and they need to blow off steam if you have a creek nearby take him there in the early evening it will be cooler there and he can splash around to cool off there is bound to be something swimming around in it he will be fascinated with the polliwogs and such it will all wash off and he will love you for it Professional wrestling match types Solar power The Marshall Mathers LP Professional wrestling aerial techniques Shaggy dog story Characters in the Smurfs Trish Stratus Tag Leon White Sumo Eddie Guerrero Episodes of Lost (Season 1) The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Professional wrestling slang Stone Cold Steve Austin Professional wrestling holds Shawn Michaels Professional wrestling throws Diving Ben Johnson (athlete